        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 3:36PM CDT by NWS Norman OK</headline>
        <description>At 336 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Goodlett, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Quanah, Chillicothe, Odell, Goodlett, and Medicine Mound.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
